OL,3,CHospital apologises after 21 patients
OL,4,Ctreated with non-sterile instruments
OL,6,FA health board has apologised after 21
OL,7,Fpatients were treated using
OL,8,Funsterilised instruments at the Royal
OL,9,FGwent Hospital in Newport.
OL,11,FThe incident has left these patients
OL,12,Fat risk of infection of blood-borne
OL,13,Fviruses, although the risk has been
OL,14,Fdescribed as "extremely low".
OL,16,FThe most common blood-borne viruses
OL,17,Finclude HIV, Hepatitis B and Hepatitis
OL,18,FC.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G1/6
